The national coordinator, Maik-kings Associates, a Non-governmental Organization (NGO), Dr. Kingsley Ogbonnaya has said that there was no jubilation over the Supreme Court affirmation of governor Okezie Ikpeazu’s re-election as governor of Abia State. Ogbonnaya who stated this in an exclusive interview with LEADERSHIP yesterday in Abuja, said that the judgment of Supreme Court was not in the favour of the people. He said, “Abians who cut across the country have been reacting to the ruling of the supreme court that affirmed governor Okezie Ikpeazu re-election as governor of Abia State, can’t help the people. “Sincerely speaking, we the Abians are not in any jubilation mood because there is no meaningful development going on in the state. “The people are not excited at all about the ruling,” he said According to him, from Abia North to Abia Central, down to his home base Abia South Senatorial Zone of thousands of Abians are not happy over the landmark judgement. He added that governor Ikpeazu himself can’t celebrate his victory in the state.